item.title: Need help getting my server online! Please help!
item.dc:creator: @I_need_a_username I need a username
item.description:
@I_need_a_username wrote:

184.#.#.# would be your WAN (Wide Are Network)

192.#.#.# would be your LAN ip (Local Area Network)

your LAN ip, is simply for your connection at your house, not around the world

your WAN ip, is for the world to see, and possibly use

Mybe thats the problem?... But idk on the webclient creater page it says neither ips r online...
Did you use 184.#.#.# or 192.#.#.# if you used 192.#.#.# DONT >> 184.#.#.# is the right one <<
Or is there another way to portfoward it?
Use UTORRENT to portforward theres a tut floating around somewhere
